diff --git a/SOLUTION.md b/SOLUTION.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..e521c69
--- /dev/null
+++ b/SOLUTION.md
@@ -0,0 +1,14 @@
+# Solution
+
+Two bugs in `lrucache/cache.py`:
+
+1. **`get` did not refresh recency.** A cache hit returned the value but left the
+   entry's position in the `OrderedDict` unchanged, so recently-read entries were
+   still treated as least-recently-used and got evicted. Fix: call
+   `self._data.move_to_end(key)` on a hit.
+
+2. **`put` evicted an entry even when updating an existing key.** The capacity
+   check ran unconditionally, so re-putting a key already in a full cache evicted
+   the LRU entry before overwriting in place (which never grows the cache). Fix:
+   only evict when the key is new and the cache is at capacity
+   (`if key not in self._data and len(self._data) >= self.capacity`).
